AJ&pg=PA8|date=2013|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=978-1-4094-9364-8}}\n* {{cite book|last=Eigeldinger|first=Jean-Jacques|authorlink = Jean-Jacques Eigeldinger| title=Chopin: Pianist and Teacher: As Seen by his Pupils|year=1988|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge|isbn=978-0-521-36709-7}}\n* Ferguson, Howard (1980). \"Study\", in [[Stanley Sadie]] (ed.), ''[[The New Grove Dictionary of Music and Musicians]]'', London: Macmillan, vol. 18, pp.&nbsp;304\u201305.\n* Golos, George S. (1960). \"Some Slavic Predecessors of Chopin\" in ''[[The Musical Quarterly]]'' vol. 46 no. 4, pp.&nbsp;437\u201347.\n* {{cite book|last=Goldberg|first=Halina|title=The Age of Chopin: Interdisciplinary Inquiries|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lPSSMhdW_bQC&pg=PA88|year=2004|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=978-0-253-21628-1}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hall-Swadley|first=Janita R. |title=The Collected Writings of Franz Liszt: F. Chopin|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DrivAkWuo8cC&pg=PA32|date=15 July 2011|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-1-4616-6409-3}}\n* Hamilton, Kenneth (2008). ''After the Golden Age: Romantic Pianism and Modern Performance''. Oxford: Oxford University Press. {{ISBN|978-0-19-517826-5}}\n* [[Arthur Hedley|Hedley, Arthur]] ''et al.'' (2005). \"Chopin, Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric (Fran\u00e7ois),\" ''[[Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica]]'', 15th ed., vol. 3, pp.&nbsp;263\u201364.\n* Hedley, Arthur and Maurice Brown (1980). \"Chopin, Fryderyk Franciszek [Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Fran\u00e7ois]\", sections 1\u20136 in [[Stanley Sadie|S. Sadie]] (ed.) ''[[The New Grove Dictionary of Music and Musicians]]'', London: Macmillan, vol. 4, pp.&nbsp;292\u201398.\n* Hutchings, A.G.B. (1968). \"The Romantic Era\", in Alec Robertson and Denis Stevens (eds.), ''The Pelican History of Music 3: Classical and Romantic'', Harmondsworth: Penguin Books, pp.&nbsp;99\u2013139.\n* {{cite encyclopedia |last=Jachimecki|first=Zdzis\u0142aw|authorlink=Zdzis\u0142aw Jachimecki|ti